{
  "texts": [
    "Our choice for RF is due to its ability to reduce overfitting, to address imbalanced datasets, and yield a vigorous prediction accuracy [37]- [39].",
    "Literature ReviewA study [40] proposed a novel feature-based deep learning architecture for fraud detection.",
    "It explored a homogeneous behavior analysis to profile user behavioral data.",
    "So, it uses a cardholder's personal identification number to authenticate associated transactions and checks against the database to ensure accuracy before using each credit card.",
    "The study [41], as extended by [42] investigated credit card fraud detection using a spatiotemporal data while focusing on real-time credit card transactions."
  ]
}